th policy mirror\n  28Ôćĺ- Unit tests in `tests/pipeline-infra/` and `tests/services/`\n  29Ôćĺ- Integration tests in `tests/integration/f001-user-stories.integration.test.js`\n  30Ôćĺ- Documentation in `.prizm-docs/runtime/pipeline-infra.prizm` and `.prizm-docs/pipeline/scripts.prizm`\n  31Ôćĺ\n  32Ôćĺ### Acceptance Criteria Met\n  33Ôćĺ\n  34Ôćĺ- US-1: Unified config loading with readable validation errors\n  35Ôćĺ- US-2: Standard directory structure with Python/JS parity\n  36Ôćĺ- US-3: Unified script execution API (run/status/stop/logs/retry/reset)\n  37Ôćĺ- US-4: TypeScript and ESLint baseline established\n  38Ôćĺ\n  39Ôćĺ### Verification\n  40Ôćĺ\n  41Ôćĺ- `npm run typecheck`: 0 errors\n  42Ôćĺ- `npm run lint`: 0 warnings\n  43Ôćĺ- `npm test`: 29 tests pass\n  44Ôćĺ\n  45Ôćĺ---\n  46Ôćĺ\n  47Ôćĺ## F-002: Telegram Pipeline Command Router\n  48Ôćĺ\n  49Ôćĺ**Status:** completed  \n  50Ôćĺ**Completion Date:** 2026-03-12\n  51Ôćĺ\n  52Ôćĺ### Deliverables\n  53Ôćĺ\n  54Ôćĺ- `src/bot/commands/index.js` - Router entry point (auth, parse, validate, dispatch)\n  55Ôćĺ- `src/bot/commands/parser.js` - Command parsing with alias support\n  56Ôćĺ- `src/bot/commands/registry.js` - Dynamic command registration\n  57Ôćĺ- `src/bot/commands/validator.js` - Parameter validation\n  58Ôćĺ- `src/bot/commands/formatter.js` - User-friendly error messages\n  59Ôćĺ- `src/bot/commands/help.js` - Dynamic help text generation\n  60Ôćĺ- `src/bot/commands/handlers/pipeline.js` - Pipeline command handler\n  61Ôćĺ- `src/bot/commands/handlers/bugfix.js` - Bugfix shortcut handler\n  62Ôćĺ- `src/bot/commands/handlers/planner.js` - Planner pipeline handler\n  63Ôćĺ- `src/bot/commands/handlers/status.js` - Status query handler\n  64Ôćĺ- `src/bot/commands/handlers/logs.js` - Logs query handler\n  65Ôćĺ- `src/bot/commands/handlers/stop.js` - Stop pipeline handler\n  66Ôćĺ- Unit tests in `tests/bot/commands/`\n  67Ôćĺ- Integration tests in `tests/integration/f002-command-router.integration.test.js`\n  68Ôćĺ- Documentation in `.prizm-docs/runtime/bot.prizm`\n  69Ôćĺ\n  70Ôćĺ### Acceptance Criteria Met\n  71Ôćĺ\n  72Ôćĺ- US-1: Pipeline command with run/status/logs/stop subcommands\n  73Ôćĺ- US-2: Bugfix command as shortcut to `/pipeline run --type=bugfix`\n  74Ôćĺ- US-3: Status query showing all running pipelines\n  75Ôćĺ- US-4: Logs query with file fallback for large output\n  76Ôćĺ- US-5: Stop pipeline with confirmation\n  77Ôćĺ- US-6: Error guidance with clear suggestions\n  78Ôćĺ- US-7: Authorization guard on all commands\n  79Ôćĺ\n  80Ôćĺ### Commands Implemented\n  81Ôćĺ\n  82Ôćĺ| Command | Aliases | Description |\n  83Ôćĺ|---------|---------|-------------|\n  84Ôćĺ| `/pipeline` | `/p` | Manage pipelines (run/status/logs/stop) |\n  85Ôćĺ| `/bugfix` | `/b` | Start bugfix pipeline |\n  86Ôćĺ| `/planner` | ÔÇö | Manage planner pipelines |\n  87Ôćĺ| `/status` | `/s` | Show running pipelines |\n  88Ôćĺ| `/logs` | `/l` | View pipeline logs |\n  89Ôćĺ| `/stop` | ÔÇö | Stop running pipelines |\n  90Ôćĺ\n  91Ôćĺ### Verification\n  92Ôćĺ\n  93Ôćĺ- `npm test`: 105 tests pass (76 for F-002)\n  94Ôćĺ- Code review: PASS\n  95Ôćĺ- All 21 tasks completed\n  96Ôćĺ\n  97Ôćĺ---\n  98Ôćĺ\n  99Ôćĺ## F-003: Feature and Bug Plan Ingestion\n 100Ôćĺ\n 101Ôćĺ**Status:** completed  \n 102Ôćĺ**Completion Date:** 2026-03-12\n 103Ôćĺ\n 104Ôćĺ### Deliverables\n 105Ôćĺ\n 106Ôćĺ- `src/services/plan-ingestion-service.js` - Schema validation, version management, plan registry\n 107Ôćĺ- `src/bot/commands/handlers/plan.js` - Plan command handler (status/versions/use/rollback/validate)\n 108Ôćĺ- `src/bot/telegram.js` - Document upload handler for JSON files\n 109Ôćĺ- `src/services/pipeline-control-service.js` - Extended with resolvePlanListPath()\n 110Ôćĺ- `src/pipeline-infra/config-loader.js` - Extended with plansDir config\n 111Ôćĺ- `plans/` directory structure with feature-list/ and bug-fix-list/ subdirectories\n 112Ôćĺ- Unit tests in `tests/services/plan-ingestion-service.test.js`\n 113Ôćĺ- Integration tests in `tests/integration/f003-plan-ingestion.integration.test.js`\n 114Ôćĺ\n 115Ôćĺ### Acceptance Criteria Met\n 116Ôćĺ\n 117Ôćĺ- US-1: Upload Plan File - Telegram document message handling with auto-type detection\n 118Ôćĺ- US-2: Schema Validation - Ajv-based validation with field-level error messages\n 119Ôćĺ- US-3: Version Management - Timestamp-based versioning with use/rollback commands\n 120Ôćĺ- US-4: Plan Status Query - Status command showing version info and content summary\n 121Ôćĺ- US-5: Plan Integrity Protection - Validation precedes save, current version preserved on error\n 122Ôćĺ- US-6: Pipeline Integration - resolvePlanListPath() for dynamic plan path resolution\n 123Ôćĺ\n 124Ôćĺ### Commands Implemented\n 125Ôćĺ\n 126Ôćĺ| Command | Subcommands | Description |\n 127Ôćĺ|---------|-------------|-------------|\n 128Ôćĺ| `/plan` | status, versions, use, rollback, validate | Manage plan files |\n 129Ôćĺ\n 130Ôćĺ### Verification\n 131Ôćĺ\n 132Ôćĺ- Code review: PASS_WITH_WARNINGS\n 133Ôćĺ- All 18 tasks completed\n 134Ôćĺ- Unit tests: 19 passing\n 135Ôćĺ- Integration tests: 10 passing\n 136Ôćĺ\n 137Ôćĺ---\n 138Ôćĺ\n 139Ôćĺ## F-004: Pipeline Process Controller\n 140Ôćĺ\n 141Ôćĺ**Status:** completed\n 142Ôćĺ**Completion Date:** 2026-03-12\n 143Ôćĺ\n 144Ôćĺ### Deliverables\n 145Ôćĺ\n 146Ôćĺ- `src/pipeline-infra/lock-manager.js` - File-based lock management with PID validation\n 147Ôćĺ- `src/pipeline-infra/state-manager.js` - State file reading/writing for daemon and pipeline state\n 148Ôćĺ- `src/pipeline-infra/error-codes.js` - Extended with 6 new error codes for F-004\n 149Ôćĺ- `src/pipeline-infra/path-policy.js` - Extended with lock/state path resolvers\n 150Ôćĺ- `src/services/pipeline-controller.js` - Unified pipeline control API with concurrency protection\n 151Ôćĺ- `src/bot/commands/handlers/pipeline.js` - Updated to use pipeline-controller\n 152Ôćĺ- `src/bot/commands/handlers/status.js` - Updated to use pipeline-controller\n 153Ôćĺ- `src/bot/commands/handlers/logs.js` - Updated to use pipeline-controller\n 154Ôćĺ- `src/bot/commands/handlers/stop.js` - Updated to use pipeline-controller\n 155Ôćĺ- Unit tests in `tests/pipeline-infra/lock-manager.test.js` and `tests/pipeline-infra/state-manager.test.js`\n 156Ôćĺ- Unit tests in `tests/services/pipeline-controller.test.js`\n 157Ôćĺ- Integration tests in `tests/integration/f004-pipeline-controller.integration.test.js`\n 158Ôćĺ\n 159Ôćĺ### Acceptance Criteria Met\n 160Ôćĺ\n 161Ôćĺ- US-1: Unified Pipeline Start - startPipeline with daemon/foreground modes, lock acquisition\n 162Ôćĺ- US-2: Pipeline Stop - stopPipeline with ALREADY_STOPPED handling, lock release\n 163Ôćĺ- US-3: Target Retry - retryTarget with validation and mode support\n 164Ôćĺ- US-4: Run Single Feature - runSingle without lock (independent execution)\n 165Ôćĺ- US-5: Status Query - getStatus with daemon/pipeline state, lastResult\n 166Ôćĺ- US-6: Logs Query - getLogs with line limit, missing file handling\n 167Ôćĺ- US-7: Concurrency Protection - lock-manager with stale lock cleanup, forceUnlock\n 168Ôćĺ- US-8: Error Mapping - Consistent error codes with hint/context fields\n 169Ôćĺ- US-9: Telegram Handler Integration - All handlers updated to use pipeline-controller\n 170Ôćĺ\n 171Ôćĺ### Error Codes Added\n 172Ôćĺ\n 173Ôćĺ| Code | Description |\n 174Ôćĺ|------|-------------|\n 175Ôćĺ| LOCK_ACQUISITION_FAILED | Pipeline already running |\n 176Ôćĺ| ALREADY_STOPPED | Pipeline not running |\n 177Ôćĺ| PIPELINE_NOT_RUNNING | No active pipeline |\n 178Ôćĺ| INVALID_TARGET | Missing or invalid target ID |\n 179Ôćĺ| TARGET_NOT_RETRYABLE | Target state not retryable |\n 180Ôćĺ| DAEMON_START_FAILED | Failed to start daemon |\n 181Ôćĺ\n 182Ôćĺ### Key Decisions\n 183Ôćĺ\n 184Ôćĺ- D1: File lock + PID validation for concurrency protection (no external dependencies)\n 185Ôćĺ- D2: Separate lock-manager module for single responsibility\n 186Ôćĺ- D3: Reuse existing state files (backward compatible)\n 187Ôćĺ- D4: New pipeline-controller module vs extending pipeline-control-service\n 188Ôćĺ- D5: runSingle does NOT acquire lock (independent execution)\n 189Ôćĺ\n 190Ôćĺ### Verification\n 191Ôćĺ\n 192Ôćĺ- Code review: PASS\n 193Ôćĺ- 128 of 143 tasks completed (core functionality complete)\n 194Ôćĺ- Unit tests: 80+ passing\n 195Ôćĺ- Integration tests: 20+ passing\n 196Ôćĺ\n 197Ôćĺ---\n 198Ôćĺ\n 199Ôćĺ## F-005: Pipeline Status Aggregation and Log Streaming\n 200Ôćĺ\n 201Ôćĺ**Status:** completed\n 202Ôćĺ**Completion Date:** 2026-03-13\n 203Ôćĺ\n 204Ôćĺ### Deliverables\n 205Ôćĺ\n 206Ôćĺ- `src/services/status-aggregator.js` - Aggregates state from multiple sources for unified status view\n 207Ôćĺ- `src/services/log-pager.js` - Paginated log reading with streaming support for large files\n 208Ôćĺ- `src/services/telegram-pusher.js` - Telegram message pushing with throttling, chunking, heartbeat\n 209Ôćĺ- `src/services/index.js` - Exports all new services\n 210Ôćĺ- `src/bot/commands/handlers/status.js` - Updated with aggregated status and --type parameter\n 211Ôćĺ- `src/bot/commands/handlers/logs.js` - Updated with pagination (--lines, --offset, --file)\n 212Ôćĺ- `src/pipeline-infra/error-codes.js` - Extended with 8 new error codes for F-005\n 213Ôćĺ- `src/services/pipeline-controller.js` - Extended with lifecycle hooks (on/off/emit)\n 214Ôćĺ- Unit tests in `tests/services/status-aggregator.test.js`, `tests/services/log-pager.test.js`, `tests/services/telegram-pusher.test.js`\n 215Ôćĺ- Integration tests in `tests/integration/f005-status-and-logs.integration.test.js`\n 216Ôćĺ\n 217Ôćĺ### Acceptance Criteria Met\n 218Ôćĺ\n 219Ôćĺ- US-1: Aggregated Status Query - /status shows running/paused/completed/failed/idle state with progress\n 220Ôćĺ- US-2: Paginated Logs Query - /logs with --lines, --offset, --type parameters (max 500 lines)\n 221Ôćĺ- US-3: Message Length Compliance - Auto-chunking at 4000 chars with [N/M] segment numbering\n 222Ôćĺ- US-4: Heartbeat Progress Push - Event-driven heartbeat with 30s throttle\n 223Ôćĺ- US-5: Error Summary Push - Error notifications with log lines and duration\n 224Ôćĺ- US-6: Diagnostic Error Messages - Friendly messages for missing/corrupted state files\n 225Ôćĺ\n 226Ôćĺ### Commands Enhanced\n 227Ôćĺ\n 228Ôćĺ| Command | New Parameters | Description |\n 229Ôćĺ|---------|----------------|-------------|\n 230Ôćĺ| `/status` | `--type=feature\\|bugfix` | Aggregated pipeline status |\n 231Ôćĺ| `/logs` | `--lines=N --offset=N --type=feature\\|bugfix --file` | Paginated log viewing |\n 232Ôćĺ\n 233Ôćĺ### Error Codes Added\n 234Ôćĺ\n 235Ôćĺ| Code | Description |\n 236Ôćĺ|------|-------------|\n 237Ôćĺ| STATE_FILE_MISSING | State file not found |\n 238Ôćĺ| STATE_FILE_CORRUPTED | JSON parse error |\n 239Ôćĺ| LOG_FILE_MISSING | Log file not found |\n 240Ôćĺ| LOG_READ_ERROR | Log read failure |\n 241Ôćĺ| SEND_FAILED | Telegram send failure |\n 242Ôćĺ| FILE_SEND_FAILED | File send failure |\n 243Ôćĺ| HEARTBEAT_DISABLED | Heartbeat not enabled |\n 244Ôćĺ| INVALID_PIPELINE_TYPE | Invalid pipeline type |\n 245Ôćĺ\n 246Ôćĺ### Key Decisions\n 247Ôćĺ\n 248Ôćĺ- D1: Independent status-aggregator service (single responsibility)\n 249Ôćĺ- D2: In-memory message queue with retry (non-blocking)\n 250Ôćĺ- D3: CLI argument pagination (simple, no complex protocol)\n 251Ôćĺ- D4: Event-driven heartbeat + time throttle (30s minimum interval)\n 252Ôćĺ- D5: Real-time error extraction from logs (no additional storage)\n 253Ôćĺ- D6: Lifecycle hooks via EventEmitter in pipeline-controller\n 254Ôćĺ- D7: Message retry: max 3, exponential backoff (1s Ôćĺ 2s Ôćĺ 4s)\n 255Ôćĺ\n 256Ôćĺ### Verification\n 257Ôćĺ\n 258Ôćĺ- All 77 tasks completed\n 259Ôćĺ- Unit tests: 120+ passing\n 260Ôćĺ- Integration tests: 15+ passing\n 261Ôćĺ- NFR-1: Status aggregation < 200ms, log read < 300ms\n 262Ôćĺ- NFR-2: Push failures don't block pipeline (queue + retry)\n 263Ôćĺ- NFR-3: Test coverage > 85%\n 264Ôćĺ\n 265Ôćĺ---\n 266Ôćĺ\n 267Ôćĺ## F-006: Safety and Permission Guard\n 268Ôćĺ\n 269Ôćĺ**Status:** completed\n 270Ôćĺ**Completion Date:** 2026-03-12\n 271Ôćĺ\n 272Ôćĺ### Deliverables\n 273Ôćĺ\n 274Ôćĺ- `src/security/permission-guard.js` - Three-tier permission model (admin/operator/viewer) with env config\n 275Ôćĺ- `src/security/param-sanitizer.js` - Parameter sanitization with path traversal and shell injection protection\n 276Ôćĺ- `src/security/confirmation-manager.js` - Text-based confirmation flow with 60s timeout\n 277Ôćĺ- `src/security/guard.js` - Unified guard middleware for command handlers\n 278Ôćĺ- `src/security/system-guard.js` - System exec command guard with ENABLE_SYSTEM_EXEC control\n 279Ôćĺ- `src/security/index.js` - Module exports\n 280Ôćĺ- `src/services/audit-log-service.js` - JSON Lines audit logging with rotation (10MB/5 files)\n 281Ôćĺ- `src/bot/commands/handlers/audit.js` - /audit command for log query (admin-only)\n 282Ôćĺ- `src/bot/commands/handlers/pipeline.js` - Updated with force-unlock, confirmation flow, audit logging\n 283Ôćĺ- `src/bot/commands/handlers/stop.js` - Updated with confirmation flow\n 284Ôćĺ- `src/config.js` - Extended with security configuration\n 285Ôćĺ- `.env.example` - Updated with USER_PERMISSIONS, AUDIT_LOG_* vars\n 286Ôćĺ- Unit tests in `tests/security/`\n 287Ôćĺ- Unit tests in `tests/services/audit-log-service.test.js`\n 288Ôćĺ- Integration tests in `tests/integration/security-flow.test.js`, `tests/integration/security-extended.test.js`\n 289Ôćĺ- Documentation in `.prizm-docs/runtime/security.prizm`\n 290Ôćĺ\n 291Ôćĺ### Acceptance Criteria Met\n 292Ôćĺ\n 293Ôćĺ- US-1: User Permission Levels - Three-tier model (admin/operator/viewer) with USER_PERMISSIONS env config\n 294Ôćĺ- US-2: High-Risk Command Authorization - stop/reset/force-unlock require admin, retry requires operator\n 295Ôćĺ- US-3: Parameter Sanitization - Path traversal, shell injection, and dangerous character protection\n 296Ôćĺ- US-4: Confirmation for Sensitive Actions - Text-based CONFIRM with 60s timeout, --force for admin\n 297Ôćĺ- US-5: Audit Logging - JSON Lines format with rotation, query by user/time/action\n 298Ôćĺ\n 299Ôćĺ### High-Risk Command Matrix\n 300Ôćĺ\n 301Ôćĺ| Command | Min Permission | Confirmation |\n 302Ôćĺ|---------|---------------|--------------|\n 303Ôćĺ| `stop` | admin | Yes (--force skips) |\n 304Ôćĺ| `reset` | admin | Yes (--force skips) |\n 305Ôćĺ| `retry` | operator | No |\n 306Ôćĺ| `exec` | admin | No (ENABLE_SYSTEM_EXEC) |\n 307Ôćĺ| `force-unlock` | admin | Yes (--force skips) |\n 308Ôćĺ\n 309Ôćĺ### Key Decisions\n 310Ôćĺ\n 311Ôćĺ- D1: Three-tier permission model (admin/operator/viewer)\n 312Ôćĺ- D2: Text-based confirmation (\"CONFIRM\") instead of inline keyboard\n 313Ôćĺ- D3: JSON Lines audit log format with rotation\n 314Ôćĺ- D4: --force flag only for admin users\n 315Ôćĺ\n 316Ôćĺ### Verification\n 317Ôćĺ\n 318Ôćĺ- Code review: PASS_WITH_WARNINGS\n 319Ôćĺ- All 22 tasks completed\n 320Ôćĺ- Unit tests: 90+ passing\n 321Ôćĺ- Integration tests: 43+ passing\n 322Ôćĺ\n 323Ôćĺ---\n 324Ôćĺ\n 325Ôćĺ## F-007: Test and Validation Suite\n 326Ôćĺ\n 327Ôćĺ**Status:** completed  \n 328Ôćĺ**Completion Date:** 2026-03-12\n 329Ôćĺ\n 330Ôćĺ### Deliverables\n 331Ôćĺ\n 332Ôćĺ- `tests/fixtures/plans/` - Valid and invalid plan file fixtures for validation tests\n 333Ôćĺ- `tests/fixtures/states/` - Pipeline state fixtures (idle, running, completed, failed)\n 334Ôćĺ- `tests/helpers/fixture-loader.js` - Lazy-loading utility for test fixtures\n 335Ôćĺ- `tests/helpers/mock-runner.js` - Mock script runner with response sequencing\n 336Ôćĺ- `tests/helpers/mock-telegram.js` - Mock Telegraf context for command handler tests\n 337Ôćĺ- `tests/helpers/test-state.js` - Temporary state management for integration tests\n 338Ôćĺ- `tests/integration/e2e-main-chain.test.js` - E2E test for start Ôćĺ status Ôćĺ stop main chain\n 339Ôćĺ- `tests/integration/plan-version-flow.test.js` - Integration test for plan version management\n 340Ôćĺ- Enhanced tests in `tests/bot/commands/`, `tests/services/`, `tests/security/`\n 341Ôćĺ\n 342Ôćĺ### Acceptance Criteria Met\n 343Ôćĺ\n 344Ôćĺ- US-1: Command Parsing & Routing Tests - Parser, registry, validator, formatter coverage\n 345Ôćĺ- US-2: Control Layer Return Tests - Pipeline control service, controller, plan ingestion coverage\n 346Ôćĺ- US-3: E2E Integration Test - start Ôćĺ status Ôćĺ stop main chain with state transitions\n 347Ôćĺ- US-4: Plan File Validation Tests - Schema validation, version management, dynamic switching\n 348Ôćĺ- US-5: Permission & Security Negative Tests - Permission boundaries, param sanitization, confirmation flow\n 349Ôćĺ\n 350Ôćĺ### Test Infrastructure\n 351Ôćĺ\n 352Ôćĺ| Component | Tests | Status |\n 353Ôćĺ|-----------|-------|--------|\n 354Ôćĺ| Test helpers (4 files) | 31 | Ôťů Pass |\n 355Ôćĺ| E2E main chain | 10 | Ôťů Pass |\n 356Ôćĺ| Plan version flow | 17 | Ôťů Pass |\n 357Ôćĺ| Enhanced unit tests | 150+ | Ôťů Pass |\n 358Ôćĺ\n 359Ôćĺ### Key Decisions\n 360Ôćĺ\n 361Ôćĺ- D1: Use Node.js built-in test runner (no Jest)\n 362Ôćĺ- D2: Mock runner supports response sequencing for state transitions\n 363Ôćĺ- D3: Integration tests use temp directories with cleanup\n 364Ôćĺ- D4: Fixtures version-controlled alongside schema files\n 365Ôćĺ\n 366Ôćĺ### Verification\n 367Ôćĺ\n 368Ôćĺ- Code review: PASS\n 369Ôćĺ- 37 of 40 tasks completed (core functionality complete)\n 370Ôćĺ- Test suite: 200+ tests passing\n 371Ôćĺ- NFR-1: Unit tests < 10s, Integration tests < 60s\n 372Ôćĺ\n 373Ôćĺ---\n 374Ôćĺ\n 375Ôćĺ## F-008: Commit Workflow Integration\n 376Ôćĺ\n 377Ôćĺ**Status:** completed  \n 378Ôćĺ**Completion Date:** 2026-03-15\n 379Ôćĺ\n 380Ôćĺ### Deliverables\n 381Ôćĺ\n 382Ôćĺ- `src/services/git-service.js` - Git operations wrapper using simple-git library\n 383Ôćĺ- `src/services/commit-service.js` - Commit workflow orchestration with validation, execution, recording\n 384Ôćĺ- `src/services/session-store.js` - Extended with commit tracking (addCommit/getCommits/getLastCommit)\n 385Ôćĺ- `src/bot/commands/handlers/commit.js` - /commit command handler with --message, --amend, --force\n 386Ôćĺ- `src/bot/commands/handlers/commits.js` - /commits command handler for session commit history\n 387Ôćĺ- `src/security/permission-guard.js` - Extended with commit/amend/force permission matrix\n 388Ôćĺ- `src/bot/telegram.js` - Command registration for /commit and /commits\n 389Ôćĺ- Unit tests in `tests/services/git-service.test.js`, `tests/services/commit-service.test.js`\n 390Ôćĺ- Unit tests in `tests/bot/commands/handlers/commit.test.js`, `tests/bot/commands/handlers/commits.test.js`\n 391Ôćĺ- Documentation in `.prizm-docs/runtime/services.prizm`\n 392Ôćĺ\n 393Ôćĺ### Acceptance Criteria Met\n 394Ôćĺ\n 395Ôćĺ- US-1: Telegram Commit Trigger - /commit command with --message parameter, --amend (admin only), returns commit hash\n 396Ôćĺ- US-2: Pre-Commit Validation - Pipeline status check, test status check, git status check, conflict detection\n 397Ôćĺ- US-3: Commit Result Feedback - Success: hash/author/time/files; Failure: error + suggestion; Nothing to commit: warning\n 398Ôćĺ- US-4: Session Commit Tracking - Commits stored in session, /commits command shows history, /status shows last commit\n 399Ôćĺ- US-5: High-Risk Commit Protection - --amend/--force require admin + confirmation, all ops logged to audit (AC-5.3)\n 400Ôćĺ\n 401Ôćĺ### Commands Implemented\n 402Ôćĺ\n 403Ôćĺ| Command | Aliases | Min Role | Description |\n 404Ôćĺ|---------|---------|----------|-------------|\n 405Ôćĺ| `/commit` | `/c` | operator | Commit code changes |\n 406Ôćĺ| `/commit --amend` | ÔÇö | admin | Amend last commit (requires confirmation) |\n 407Ôćĺ| `/commit --force` | ÔÇö | admin | Skip pre-commit validation (requires confirmation) |\n 408Ôćĺ| `/commits` | `/history` | viewer | View session commit history |\n 409Ôćĺ\n 410Ôćĺ### Key Decisions\n 411Ôćĺ\n 412Ôćĺ- D1: Use simple-git library for git operations (avoid shell injection)\n 413Ôćĺ- D2: Pre-commit validation includes dual check (pipeline + t