endCommit/getLastCommit/getCommitLog/getShortHash\n  31Ôćĺ- commit service (F-008): createCommitService -> validatePreConditions/commit/recordCommit/getSessionCommits/checkPipelineStatus/checkTestStatus/buildCommitMessage\n  32Ôćĺ\n  33ÔćĺTRAPS:\n  34Ôćĺ- chat operations are serialized by session key; keep async queue semantics unchanged\n  35Ôćĺ- pipeline-control-service must delegate to script-runner instead of shell string concatenation\n  36Ôćĺ- pipeline-controller must use lock-manager for concurrency protection (F-004)\n  37Ôćĺ- runSingle must NOT acquire lock (independent execution, D5)\n  38Ôćĺ\n  39ÔćĺDECISIONS:\n  40Ôćĺ- 2026-03-10 | f001-pipeline-service | expose logs/reset methods in pipeline-control-service to satisfy US3 reusable control surface\n  41Ôćĺ- 2026-03-12 | f003-plan-ingestion | add plan-ingestion-service for schema validation, version management, and plan registry\n  42Ôćĺ- 2026-03-12 | f004-pipeline-controller | new module for unified pipeline control with lock management (D4)\n  43Ôćĺ- 2026-03-13 | f005-status-logs | add status-aggregator, log-pager, telegram-pusher for pipeline status aggregation and log streaming\n  44Ôćĺ- 2026-03-15 | f008-commit-workflow | add git-service and commit-service for commit workflow with pre-commit validation, audit logging (AC-5.3)\n  45Ôćĺ"}],"is_error":false}],"role":"user"},"parent_tool_use_id":"call_d540a6c2bae6447584e38f43","__timestamp":"2026-03-11T21:37:35.126Z","_requestId":"b07a63a169934f4593711d9842f5a228"}
{"type":"user","uuid":"6d1d17cc-5d02-4541-8d57-4e56c6d96f44","session_id":"b2229cc3-f35d-4fe4-8e7e-67c19086b8f2","message":{"content":[{"type":"tool_result","tool_use_id":"call_2dc9e0c3f26047dd92b8f808","content":[{"type":"text","text":"   1ÔćĺDOC_LEVEL: L2\n   2ÔćĺMODULE: bot\n   3ÔćĺPATH: src/bot/**\n   4ÔćĺDESCRIPTION: Telegram bot handlers and command routing layer\n   5Ôćĺ\n   6ÔćĺENTRYPOINT:\n   7Ôćĺ- src/bot/telegram.js -> createTelegramBot() registers all commands and handlers\n   8Ôćĺ\n   9ÔćĺKEY_FILES:\n  10Ôćĺ- src/bot/telegram.js - Main bot factory, command registration, text handler\n  11Ôćĺ- src/bot/commands/index.js - Router entry point, routeCommand()\n  12Ôćĺ- src/bot/commands/parser.js - Command text parser, parseCommand()\n  13Ôćĺ- src/bot/commands/registry.js - Command registration and lookup\n  14Ôćĺ- src/bot/commands/validator.js - Parameter validation\n  15Ôćĺ- src/bot/commands/formatter.js - Error message formatting\n  16Ôćĺ- src/bot/commands/help.js - Help text generation\n  17Ôćĺ- src/bot/commands/handlers/*.js - Individual command handlers\n  18Ôćĺ\n  19ÔćĺSUBDIRS:\n  20Ôćĺ- src/bot/commands -> command routing and dispatch\n  21Ôćĺ- src/bot/commands/handlers -> individual command implementations\n  22Ôćĺ\n  23ÔćĺINTERFACES:\n  24Ôćĺ- Telegram Commands:\n  25Ôćĺ  - /start - Bot startup greeting\n  26Ôćĺ  - /help - Dynamic help text\n  27Ôćĺ  - /reset - Clear chat session\n  28Ôćĺ  - /screenshot - Capture desktop screenshot\n  29Ôćĺ  - /exec <cmd> - Execute system command\n  30Ôćĺ  - /pipeline [action] [target] [--type=] - Pipeline management (alias: /p)\n  31Ôćĺ  - /bugfix <target> - Start bugfix pipeline (alias: /b)\n  32Ôćĺ  - /planner [action] [target] - Planner pipeline management\n  33Ôćĺ  - /status [--type=feature|bugfix] - Show aggregated pipeline status (alias: /s)\n  34Ôćĺ  - /logs [--lines=N] [--offset=N] [--type=feature|bugfix] [--file] - View pipeline logs with pagination (alias: /l)\n  35Ôćĺ  - /stop [target] - Stop pipeline\n  36Ôćĺ  - /plan [action] [type] [version] - Plan file management (status/versions/use/rollback/validate)\n  37Ôćĺ  - /commit [--message=\"...\"] [--amend] [--force] - Commit code changes with pre-commit validation (alias: /c)\n  38Ôćĺ  - /commits [--count=N] - View session commit history (alias: /history)\n  39Ôćĺ\n  40ÔćĺTRAPS:\n  41Ôćĺ- Commands require authorization via isAllowedUser()\n  42Ôćĺ- Large logs (>=4000 chars) sent as files\n  43Ôćĺ- Command parsing normalizes to lowercase\n  44Ôćĺ- Registry stores normalized command names\n  45Ôćĺ- F002-CRIT-001: Parser treats first non-option token as subcommand; validator must check if command has no subcommands and use parsed.subcommand as first positional param\n  46Ôćĺ- F-005: /status uses status-aggregator for aggregated status; /logs uses log-pager for pagination\n  47Ôćĺ- F-008: /commit requires pre-commit validation (pipeline status + test status); --amend/--force require admin + confirmation\n  48Ôćĺ\n  49ÔćĺDECISIONS:\n  50Ôćĺ- 2026-03-12 | F-002-bot-commands | Add command routing layer with parser, registry, validator for pipeline commands\n  51Ôćĺ- 2026-03-12 | F-002-alias-mapping | Support command aliases /p, /b, /s, /l\n  52Ôćĺ- 2026-03-12 | F002-CRIT-001 | Fix positional args: validator uses parsed.subcommand as first positional when command has no subcommands\n  53Ôćĺ- 2026-03-12 | F-003-plan-command | Add /plan command with status/versions/use/rollback/validate subcommands for plan file management\n  54Ôćĺ- 2026-03-13 | F-005-status-logs | Update /status and /logs to use status-aggregator and log-pager with pagination support\n  55Ôćĺ- 2026-03-15 | F-008-commit-commands | Add /commit and /commits commands with pre-commit validation, session tracking, and admin confirmation for --amend/--force\n  56Ôćĺ"}],"is_error":false}],"role":"user"},"parent_tool_use_id":"call_2dc9e0c3f26047dd92b8f808","__timestamp":"2026-03-11T21:37:35.132Z","_requestId":"b07a63a169934f4593711d9842f5a228"}
